    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose elite score of 81.88 leads the charge against Teng. His performance is buoyed by a significant +16% park factor adjustment and a +14% boost from his dynamic platoon advantage, making him our highest-upside play. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** follows closely with a 72.10 score, benefiting significantly from a favorable +10% SP skill adjustment against the matchup with Holmes. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.66) and **Kyle Tucker** (69.49) remain high-floor pillars; **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** capitalizes on a +7% platoon edge, while **Kyle Tucker** is projected for a strong day assuming he slots into the clean-up spot as expected.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench centered on **Josh Jung**, who landed just outside the cut at 50.73. While his +8% order adjustment offered some intrigue, the aggregate efficiency of our current starters\u2014particularly the platoon-favored **Josh Lowe** (68.67) and **Jacob Wilson** (64.87)\u2014outpaced his base projection. We are closely monitoring **Andy Pages** and **Kyle Tucker** due to pending official lineups; if shifts in batting order occur, we may adjust to ensure we aren't losing valuable R/RBI opportunities. While **Dominic Smith** presents the lowest score in the active lineup (48.11), his platoon advantage keeps him marginally above the bench options like **Nasim Nunez** and **Coby Mayo**, who remain sidelined to preserve our strict game-cap efficiency targets.",
